>   My Support for you as well as Sarella.</span><hr size=1> Hello all,<br>
<br>
Some of you may not know me, Some of you may not even care who I am, but I felt it was needed that I post here and explain a bit about Sarella and Clan Skallagrim.<br>
<br>
Sarella is my girl friend in real life.  Over the past several weeks I have watched her log on to EQ for a few short minutes and then usually log off depressed about one thing or another.  For the past year I have listened to her periodically rant about this person or that person not being in Clan for the guild but for the loot.<br>
<br>
Her desicion to leave Clan and join House Bloodthorne was hers and hers ALONE!  I even tried to convince her not to leave.  I have a great deal of respect for several members of Clan and remember the good old days when Xsareth (RL friends of mine) and Sare had just joined you folks.<br>
<br>
I don't know what's happened to your guild folks but I do know this; you're not the same as you used to be.  I used to look up to you as a role model for my guild because you were family and you had the balls to take on new stuff.  Now I see many of the members that I respected leaving.  Do yourselves a favor and sit back and think about what's goin' on with your guild.  You're no longer the respected guild you were.  I've been playing EQ longer than Sare and have had the pleasure of meeting many of you before you became &quot;Ubar&quot;.<br>
<br>
Sare may return to you one day but she needs a break.  The loot whoring that some folks have been doing and the extencive raid schedule has worn her thin.  There's nothing wrong with wanting to raid.  There is something wrong with forgetting that the people who are behind the keyboards have real lives too.<br>
<br>
I'm asking you folks as some one who DOES care what happens to Clan because he likes many of you and because his girl friend loves all of you.  PULL YOUR HEADS OUT OF YOUR A**ES and clean it up.  Remember, EQ is a game that people play to have fun.<br>
<br>
<br>
